{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating a cross-platform SwiftCrossUI app with Swift Bundler."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This quick start guide uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Although not strictly required, it simplifies many aspects of cross-platform distribution and provides a platform-agnostic configuration format for specifying things such as app icons and custom URL schemes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re new to Swift, we recommend starting with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"Installing-Swift-Bundler","type":"heading","text":"Installing Swift Bundler","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Follow ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler?tab=readme-ov-file#installation-","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mint"},{"text":" is the preferred installation method on macOS and Linux as of the last update to this quick start guide.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Installing-system-dependencies","type":"heading","text":"Installing system dependencies","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each backend has different requirements. In this guide we’ll use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" which uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on macOS, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on Linux, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on Windows, and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS\/tvOS. Click through the backend relevant to your machine for detailed installation requirements. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" have no system dependencies."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Using-Swift-Bundlers-SwiftCrossUI-template","type":"heading","text":"Using Swift Bundler’s SwiftCrossUI template","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Bundler provides many built-in templates; we’ll use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftCrossUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" template. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftCrossUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" template uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"DefaultBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to select the most appropriate backend at compile time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["swift bundler create HelloWorld --template SwiftCrossUI","cd HelloWorld"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"anchor":"Running-your-app","type":"heading","text":"Running your app","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Running your new app with Swift Bundler is as simple as it gets!"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["swift bundler run"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On macOS you can provide the "},{"code":"--device <device_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option to run the app on a connected iOS or tvOS device, or the "},{"code":"--simulator <simulator_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option to run the app in a simulator."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# You can use any substring of the target device name. For example,","# \"iPhone\" matches any device connected with \"iPhone\" in its name.","swift bundler run --device \"iPhone\"","swift bundler run --simulator \"iPhone 15\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"anchor":"Making-a-change","type":"heading","text":"Making a change","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sources\/HelloWorld\/HelloWorldApp.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" in an editor of your choosing. Change "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Hello, World!\""},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Hello, Earth!\""},{"type":"text","text":". Repeat the previous step to verify that your changes get reflected."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"All-done","type":"heading","text":"All done","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’re good to go! If you make something cool with SwiftCrossUI let us know so we can add your project to our showcase once the SwiftCrossUI website is up and running!"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/quick-start"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"title":"Quick start"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Getting Started","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-virtual-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/